Constants â€“ learn how to declare constants that hold values that remain unchanged throughout the execution of the program.

Example:

SET SERVEROUTPUT ON
DECLARE
a number(3):= &value;
BEGIN
    IF(a=10) THEN
        dbms_output.put_line('The given number is matched '||a);
    ELSIF(a<10) THEN 
        dbms_output.put_line('The given number is less than 10');
    ELSE
        dbms_output.put_line('The given number is greater then 10');
    END IF;
END;
